A paramedic seals a COVID-19 coronavirus disease screening test kit during a response training exercise. JOHANNESBURG - The total number of confirmed positive COVID-19 cases in South Africa stands at 97,302 with 1,930 deaths. IN NUMBERS: COVID-19 in SA The health department announced that a total of 1,328,060 tests have been conducted to date. Recoveries stand at 19,682. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.